[The diagnosis of hepatitis A is made in the laboratory by the presence of IgM anti-hepatitis A antibody. In general, elderly individuals in underdeveloped countries are not involved in HAV outbreaks, as most of the population has been infected, clinically or sub clinically, by age 10. Another water/foodborne hepatitis virus, hepatitis E, however, is more likely to affect adults.

San Miguel del Padron (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Miguel_del_Padron) is one of the 15 municipalities or boroughs (municipios in Spanish) of the city of Havana, Cuba. It is on Havana's southeastern outskirts. - Mod. LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2366960,20.]
